      "factId": "hz.web.ff94fd1f8fae45cd.fact.2",
      "kind": "bullet",
      "text": "While the Public Suffix List has no opinion on alternative root systems, the list recognizes as authoritative and complies with ICP-3: A Unique, Authoritative Root for the DNS (ICANN, September 2001), allowing TLDs under the ICANN Root as well as inclusive sub-domain entries, and cookie apexes that comply with ICP-3 in a non-discriminatory manner.",
